# Narrow defense-in-depth: owner review only on paths Renovate does NOT
# touch. Workflow YAML, Dockerfile.* FROM/digest pins, and renovate.json
# are ALL omitted so Renovate fallback PRs (on CI failure or merge
# conflict) never need manual approval — the happy path uses
# automergeType: "branch" with no PR, but the fallback path can open one.
#
# Re-broaden the moment any bot workflow (Claude, auto-fix, codegen) is
# added to the repo — at that point the threat model shifts from
# "trusted Renovate only" to "bots with write access".

.github/CODEOWNERS                       @AndriyKalashnykov
.github/actions/**                       @AndriyKalashnykov
.dockerignore                            @AndriyKalashnykov
container-structure-test.yaml            @AndriyKalashnykov
docker-compose.yml                       @AndriyKalashnykov
docs/diagrams/**                         @AndriyKalashnykov
